{"tid":1691862,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"希望各位睇一次「A Time for Choosing／決擇的時刻」 Ronald Reagan 64年演說節錄","createTime":"2019-11-03T23:30:18.000Z","updateTime":"2019-11-08T10:36:21.000Z","uid":62151,"like":40,"dislike":1,"uniUserReply":16,"replies":[{"pid":"49a9a9ef930d3e2eadfdb85ee19279bf2010e99c","tid":1691862,"uid":62151,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-11-03T23:30:18.000Z","msg":"<code>*Ronald Reagan 係美國第40任總統</code><br />\n<a href=\"https://youtu.be/qXBswFfh6AY?t=1474\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fyoutu.be%2FqXBswFfh6AY%3Ft%3D1474&d=JjpB%2FqIgFksXGEBY%2BN5axH%2B3Qbouwy6U%2BTFwRHAqvaY%3D&h=94c39ba4\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://youtu.be/qXBswFfh6AY?t=1474</a><br />\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\">預設播放起始時間為24:34</span><br />\n<br />\n<blockquote><span style=\"font-size: small;\">There is no argument over the choice between peace and war</span><br />\n在和平與戰爭兩者之中的選擇可以說是不會有爭議的<br />\n<br />\nbut there is only one guaranteed way you can have peace and you can have it in the next second<br />\n但卻有一種方法可以保證你可以在下一秒就能夠得到和平<br />\n<br />\n<span style=\"color: red;\">surrender.<br />\n投降</span><br />\n<br />\nAdmittedly there is a risk in any course we follow other than this<br />\n無可否認選擇除此之外的方法都會有一定的危險<br />\n<br />\nbut every lesson in history tells us that the greater risk lies in appeasement<br />\n但歷史告訴我們綏靖背後卻是更大的危險<br />\n<br />\nand this is the specter our well meaning liberal friends refuse to face that their policy of accommodation is appeasement<br />\n而這就是我們的民主黨朋友心中拒絕面對的事實，他們的政策是綏靖<br />\n<br />\nand it gives no choice between peace and war, only between fight or surrender<br />\n綏靖帶給我們選擇的不是和平或戰爭，而是戰鬥或投降<br />\n<br />\nIf we continue to accommodate, continue to back and retreat, <br />\n假如我們繼續遷就對方，讓步甚至撤退<br />\n<br />\neventually we have to face the final demand the ultimatum.<br />\n終有一天我們要面對來自對方的最後一個要求－最後通牒<br />\n<br />\nAnd what then? When Nikita Khrushchev has told his people he knows what our answer will be?<br />\n然後?蘇聯領導人向他的人民表示他知道我們的答覆?<br />\n <br />\nHe has told them that we are retreating under the pressure of the Cold War,<br />\n他告訴蘇聯的人民，我們因為抵受不住冷戰的壓力而退卻<br />\n<br />\nand someday when the time comes to deliver the ultimatum<br />\n當那一天到來,向我們發出那最後通牒<br />\n<br />\nour surrender will be voluntary because by that time we will have weakened from within spiritually, morally, and economically.<br />\n我們將會因為虛弱的精神，士氣和經濟，而自願性的投降<br />\n<br />\nHe believes this because from our side he has heard voices pleading for &ldquo;peace at any price&rdquo; or &ldquo;better Red than dead,&rdquo;<br />\n蘇聯對此結果將會非常有信心，因為他們能夠聽到我們的哀求＂不惜一切也要和平＂、＂共產黨也總比死亡好＂<br />\n<br />\nor as one commentator put it, he would rather &ldquo;live on his knees than die on his feet.&rdquo;<br />\n或者像是某個報導員說的一樣：&quot;『為存活而下跪總比因站穩而戰死好』<br />\n<br />\nAnd therein lies the road to war, because those voices don&rsquo;t speak for the rest of us.<br />\n但這只會帶領我們通往戰爭的路，因為這些聲音並不代表我們<br />\n<br />\nYou and I know and do not believe that life is so dear and peace so sweet as to be purchased at the price of chains and slavery.<br />\n因為你和我都清楚明白而且不相信寶貴的生命是需要用鎖鏈和奴役交換<br />\n<br />\nIf nothing in life is worth dying for, when did this begin&ndash;just in the face of this enemy?<br />\n假如一生中都沒有任何事物值得你用生命捍衛，什麼時候才會有？要當敵人站在你面前才會醒覺？<br />\n<br />\nOr should Moses have told the children of Israel to live in slavery under the pharaohs?<br />\n還是摩西應該要告訴被奴役的希伯來人繼續在法老鞭下為奴？<br />\n<br />\nShould Christ have refused the cross?<br />\n基督是否應該要背棄十字架？<br />\n<br />\nShould the patriots at Concord Bridge have thrown down their guns and refused to fire the shot heard &rsquo;round the world?<br />\n還是在北橋打響美國獨立戰爭的愛國者們應該放下他們的武器，拒絕開出那全世界都能聽到的一槍？<br />\n<br />\nThe martyrs of history were not fools, and our honored dead who gave their lives to stop the advance of the Nazis didn&rsquo;t die in vain.<br />\n歷史上的勇士不是傻瓜，那些為國捐驅的為了阻止納粹前進而付出的血汗更不是徒勞的<br />\n <br />\n<span style=\"color: red;\">Where, then, is the road to peace? Well, it&rsquo;s a simple answer after all.<br />\n那通往和平的道路到底在哪？其實答案非常簡單<br />\n<br />\nYou and I have the courage to say to our enemies, &ldquo;There is a price we will not pay.&rdquo; There is a point beyond which they must not advance.<br />\n你和我都鼓起勇氣告訴我們的敵人，在那裡有一種價值是不會被出賣的，在那裡有一條底線是不能被跨越的<br />\n<br />\nThis is the meaning in the phrase of Barry Goldwater&rsquo;s &ldquo;peace through strength.&rdquo;<br />\n這就是貝利&middot;高華德所指的「以力量求和平」<br />\n</span><br />\n</blockquote><br />\n<br />\n<span style=\"color: blue;\"><span style=\"font-size: x-large;\">各位<br />\n我地一直以來都只有兩個選擇<br />\n危險上的和平<br />\n或者<br />\n和平下被奴役<br />\n<br />\n希望各位今日,聽日,或者以後<br />\n仍然能夠作出正確選擇<br />\n</span></span>"},{"pid":"2c8687f18136a0bf0a9006edb3566f623953a051","tid":1691862,"uid":62151,"like":2,"dislike":1,"score":1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-11-03T23:30:26.000Z","msg":"槍權宣傳：<br />\n槍權確實有風險，有危險<br />\n但假如認為以和平能夠求實力，欺騙自己，當然你能夠得到和平<br />\n但鎖鏈和奴役將會是不能回避的結果<br />\n<br />\n以實力求和平，理所當然地會有一定風險<br />\n但當敵人意圖踐踏你的價值觀，越過你作為一個人的最後底線時<br />\n你能夠拿起武器，鼓起勇氣告訴你的敵人<br />\n我們不會遷就你的敵意，我們不會讓步，更不會因為恐懼而退讓<br />\n<br />\n支持槍權，不再重複犯錯<br />\n為權力歸於人民<br />\n願權力歸於人民<br />\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\"><br />\n&quot;When government fears the people, there is liberty.When the people fear the government, there is tyranny.&quot;<br />\n當政府害怕人民，那裡將有自由；當人民害怕政府，那裡只有暴政<br />\n&ldquo;I prefer dangerous freedom over peaceful slavery.&rdquo;<br />\n&ldquo;與和平的奴役相比，我更喜歡危險的自由&rdquo;<br />\n</span><br />\n<code>-Thomas Jefferso</code><br />\n<code>美國開國元勛，美國獨立宣言主要起草人，第3任美國總統</code><br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://na.cx/i/Ap2GFeV.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fna.cx%2Fi%2FAp2GFeV.jpg&h=22843361&s={SIZE}\" />"},{"pid":"79b9de4feb52cb81338ce38943091f9d9efd8dd7","tid":1691862,"uid":62151,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-11-03T23:33:49.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/smile.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"3b8302b221fa0fa4c221703d522d0b0c99404f5f","tid":1